steps.instruction:
### Prep
- Coarsely Chop the peanuts

### Steps
1.  Soften butter and cream cheese. Preheat oven to 350F. Line 2 baking sheets with nonstick foil. 
2. Whisk cream cheese, butter, egg, and fudge packet (from brownie mix) until combined
3. Gently stir (fold) in brownie mix until just combined
4. Scoop 24 (1-inch) balls of brownie mixture and place on baking sheets 2 inches apart
5. Combine peanut butter, powdered sugar, and vanilla; stir until smooth dough forms
6. Form peanut butter dough into 24 equal balls and lightly press one into the center of each brownie dough ball while slightly flattening cookies
7. Bake cookies 1012 minutes or until edges are crisp, then cool on baking sheet 23 minutes before transferring to cooling rack to cool completely. Meanwhile, chop peanuts (if using). 
8. Pour cream in microwave-safe bowl; microwave on HIGH 30 seconds or until hot
9. Add chocolate morsels; let sit 2 minutes to melt. Stir chocolate mixture until smooth and combined
10. Spread about 1 tablespoon chocolate mixture over each cookie, then sprinkle with chopped peanuts, if desired. Serve
